article.headline: (7) PENN ST 77, GEO WASHINGTON 51
article.story:
FREEPORT, The Bahamas (Ticker) -- Jess Strom had 17 points and 
three others scored in double figures for No. 7 Penn State in a
77-51 victory over George Washington in the first round of the
Junkanoo Jam.

Strom, a junior who led the Big Ten in assists last year, hit
three of five attempts from three-point land and added five
assists for the Lady Lions (2-1), who outrebounded the
Colonials, 37-27.

Tanisha Wright, who had a game-high six assists, scored 14 of
her 16 points in the first half, laying the ball in at the
buzzer to give Penn State a 43-21, halftime edge.

Jessica Brungo added 16 points for the Lady Lions and Kelly
Mazzante had 13 points and led all players with seven boards.

Ugo Oha was 8-for-10 from the free-throw line and led George
Washington (0-2) with 14 points.

Anna Montanana chipped in with 11 points for the Colonials, who
hit just three of 16 three-point attempts.
